workplace problems i'm years old tuesday and i work in a restaurant there's a older woman in her 's or so who has the same title as me but she is always yelling at me and criticising what i do and now she has got the supervisor to yell at me all the time too is there a law or something against this because i honestly don't do anything wrong and they yell at me in front of customers aswell i hate working there so much but i can't quit until i have another job i do just as good as everyone else they say i'm too slow sometimes and i am just as fast as everyone else when i'm doing the food they get mad even if there's a tiny spec of food on the counters if i don't take out plates straight away i get yelled at i cop it everytime i go to work and i am so sick of it i'm the youngest one there so i suppose thats why they do it bloody well stab them one day analyze and evaluate the situation be honest with yourself are you working below par or is your boss unfair if she is the latter there is no reason why you should continue working for that business fire them you are just wasting your time a good boss will always try to develop good people without being rude and dictatorial conversely if your work is below par and has no possibility of ever improving a good boss will terminate your services immediately so if they are keeping you they just want to behave that way to you there are millions of good jobs and good employers out there look for them work should uplift and dignify a person peace and every blessing Social rule Friends Theory of conduct Termination of employment Paul Is Dead Sin City Knots Landing Married... with Children Plame affair Seinfeld One Piece minor characters Yellow Ribbon campaign (Fiji) Management Workplace democracy STS-62 The Apprentice 2 Reservoir Dogs CPU cache Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Cosmic Era list of characters EastEnders Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Unemployment Invader Zim Ron and Fez Ethics Debugging Supply and dem